Speaker 2: Right now, push it back for another four or five months, and we can do that.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Send the other ones back to me, the ones that you will send out to you on the 19th.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I know, but then it'll go—then I'll go back into an auto pay, but it won't be every month though.

Speaker 1: That's my whole point. You know, I understand. Yeah, I don't—I don't even want to mess with it now.

Speaker 1: Envelope. Yeah. Yeah, the same package. That's what the same address is what's going to go. The address is going to—that's from Kentucky.

Speaker 2: Okay. Okay, and then get a routing number. Now, what about the first—

Speaker 1: A tracking number. Yeah. Yeah. Yeah, tracking. Yeah. Okay. That's what I'll do.

Speaker 2: But I—I don't want to do the five-month deal. I'm just—

Speaker 1: No, I—I appreciate that. I just, you know, I'm on Social Security, and I don't need no—

Speaker 2: Surprises, you know what I mean? We're pretty tight on— we're pretty tight on our—
